  "text": "The growth hormone and insulin-like growth factors (Gh/Igfs) are both, in vertebrates including fish, key factors regulating growth. Muscle and bone are widely regulated by this system and the presence of Gh and Igf1 receptors (Ghrs and Igf1Rs) and Igf isoforms as well as binding proteins (Igfbps) are well described in fish, especially in these tissues [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Moreover, in gilthead sea bream, the function of Gh/Igfs and its response to diverse",
